#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.extract_mismatch_sine.extract_mismatch_sine:1 of
msgid ""
"Extract per-channel offset, gain, and sample-skew from a TI-ADC sine capture."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.extract_mismatch_sine.extract_mismatch_sine:3 of
msgid ""
"Interleaved output. Sample ``x[n]`` belongs to channel ``n mod M`` and was "
"taken at time ``n / fs``."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.extract_mismatch_sine.extract_mismatch_sine:6 of
msgid "Number of sub-ADCs."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.calibrate_foreground.calibrate_foreground:10
#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.extract_mismatch_sine.extract_mismatch_sine:8
#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.predict_spurs.predict_spurs:7 of
msgid "Aggregate sample rate (Hz)."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.extract_mismatch_sine.extract_mismatch_sine:10 of
msgid ""
"Input-tone frequency. If None, it is estimated from the FFT of ``x`` (use "
"coherent sampling for best results)."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.extract_mismatch_sine.extract_mismatch_sine:14 of
msgid ""
"**params** -- ``gain``    : (M,) relative gain, normalized so ``mean == 1``. "
"``offset``  : (M,) DC offset per channel (same units as ``x``). "
"``skew``    : (M,) sample-skew per channel (seconds, mean zero). "
"``fin``     : float — tone frequency used for the fit. ``A``       : float — "
"fitted fundamental amplitude (mean across channels). ``phases``  : (M,) raw "
"fitted phase per channel (rad) for diagnostics."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.calibrate_foreground.calibrate_foreground:28
#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.extract_mismatch_sine.extract_mismatch_sine:23
#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.fractional_delay.fractional_delay_farrow:22
#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.fractional_delay.fractional_delay_fft:18 of
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.extract_mismatch_sine.extract_mismatch_sine:24 of
msgid ""
"The \"skew\" returned here is relative: the mean is subtracted so an overall "
"clock delay (which is not observable from a single capture) does not leak "
"into the per-channel result. Pass ``skew - skew.mean()`` upstream."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.predict_spurs.predict_spurs:1 of
msgid "Predict TI-ADC spur frequencies and magnitudes."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.predict_spurs.predict_spurs:3 of
msgid ""
"Output of :func:`extract_mismatch_sine`. Must contain ``gain``, ``offset``, "
"``skew``, and at least one of ``fin`` / ``A``; ``fin`` can also be supplied "
"via the argument below."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.predict_spurs.predict_spurs:9 of
msgid "Input-tone frequency. Defaults to ``params['fin']`` if present."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.predict_spurs.predict_spurs:11 of
msgid ""
"Signal full-scale (peak) used as the dBFS reference. If your ``x`` was "
"scaled so the ideal sine has peak amplitude ``A``, set ``full_scale = "
"A_full_scale`` — usually the converter's peak code."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.predict_spurs.predict_spurs:16 of
msgid ""
"**spurs** -- One dict per predicted spur with keys:  - ``freq_hz`` : spur "
"frequency folded to ``[0, fs/2]`` - ``kind``    : ``'offset'`` or "
"``'gain_skew'`` - ``k``       : spur index in the M-point DFT (1..M-1) - "
"``amp``     : spur amplitude in the same units as ``x`` - ``dbfs``    : spur "
"magnitude in dBFS (relative to ``full_scale``) - ``dbc``     : spur "
"magnitude in dBc (relative to fundamental)"
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.predict_spurs.predict_spurs:16 of
msgid "**spurs** -- One dict per predicted spur with keys:"
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.predict_spurs.predict_spurs:18 of
msgid "``freq_hz`` : spur frequency folded to ``[0, fs/2]``"
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.predict_spurs.predict_spurs:19 of
msgid "``kind``    : ``'offset'`` or ``'gain_skew'``"
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.predict_spurs.predict_spurs:20 of
msgid "``k``       : spur index in the M-point DFT (1..M-1)"
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.predict_spurs.predict_spurs:21 of
msgid "``amp``     : spur amplitude in the same units as ``x``"
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.predict_spurs.predict_spurs:22 of
msgid "``dbfs``    : spur magnitude in dBFS (relative to ``full_scale``)"
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.predict_spurs.predict_spurs:23 of
msgid "``dbc``     : spur magnitude in dBc (relative to fundamental)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/timeinterleave.rst:23
msgid "Correction"
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.fractional_delay.fractional_delay_fft:1 of
msgid "Apply a fractional-sample delay via DFT phase rotation."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.fractional_delay.fractional_delay_fft:3 of
msgid ""
"Output ``y[n]`` approximates ``x((n / fs) - delay_sec)`` using the sinc "
"interpolation implicit in a length-``N`` DFT. Exact for signals that are "
"periodic over their length and strictly bandlimited to ``[0, fs/2)``."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.fractional_delay.fractional_delay_fft:9 of
msgid "Delay in seconds; positive = later in time, negative = earlier."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.fractional_delay.fractional_delay_fft:11 of
msgid "Sample rate (Hz)."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.fractional_delay.fractional_delay_farrow:18
#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.fractional_delay.fractional_delay_fft:14 of
msgid "**y**"
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.fractional_delay.fractional_delay_farrow:19
#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.fractional_delay.fractional_delay_fft:15 of
msgid "ndarray, same length as ``x``."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.fractional_delay.fractional_delay_fft:19 of
msgid ""
"Because the DFT assumes periodic extension, non-periodic signals will wrap "
"around when ``|delay_sec|`` approaches the full record length. For clean "
"results near the edges, zero-pad ``x`` before calling and trim afterwards."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.fractional_delay.fractional_delay_farrow:1 of
msgid "Apply a fractional-sample delay via a Lagrange FIR interpolator."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.fractional_delay.fractional_delay_farrow:3 of
msgid ""
"Causal / streaming alternative to :func:`fractional_delay_fft`. The "
"``n_taps``-tap centered filter trades accuracy against boundary transient "
"length (``n_taps // 2`` samples on each end are unreliable, because the "
"`same`-mode convolution zero-pads the input edges)."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.fractional_delay.fractional_delay_farrow:14 of
msgid ""
"Must be a positive odd integer. 5–9 is typical; higher = flatter passband "
"but longer transient."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.fractional_delay.fractional_delay_farrow:23 of
msgid ""
"The delay is split into an integer part (applied by zero-padded shift) and a "
"fractional remainder in ``(-0.5, 0.5]`` handled by the centered Lagrange "
"filter. When ``delay_sec == 0`` the filter is an impulse at the center tap."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.calibrate_foreground.calibrate_foreground:1 of
msgid "Apply offset / gain / skew corrections to a TI-ADC interleaved capture."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.calibrate_foreground.calibrate_foreground:3 of
msgid "Interleaved time series."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.calibrate_foreground.calibrate_foreground:5 of
msgid "Sub-ADC count."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.calibrate_foreground.calibrate_foreground:7 of
msgid ""
"Output of :func:`extract_mismatch_sine`. Required keys: ``offset``, "
"``gain``, ``skew``."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.calibrate_foreground.calibrate_foreground:12 of
msgid ""
"How to apply the fractional-sample skew correction:  - ``'fft'``   — per-"
"channel DFT phase rotation. Near machine-precision   accuracy for signals "
"with energy strictly below ``fs/(2M)``; circular   wrap at record "
"boundaries. - ``'farrow'`` — per-channel Lagrange FIR. Causal and streaming-"
"friendly.   Accuracy and boundary transient length are set by ``n_taps``."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.calibrate_foreground.calibrate_foreground:12 of
msgid "How to apply the fractional-sample skew correction:"
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.calibrate_foreground.calibrate_foreground:14 of
msgid ""
"``'fft'``   — per-channel DFT phase rotation. Near machine-precision "
"accuracy for signals with energy strictly below ``fs/(2M)``; circular wrap "
"at record boundaries."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.calibrate_foreground.calibrate_foreground:17 of
msgid ""
"``'farrow'`` — per-channel Lagrange FIR. Causal and streaming-friendly. "
"Accuracy and boundary transient length are set by ``n_taps``."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.calibrate_foreground.calibrate_foreground:20 of
msgid ""
"Only consulted when ``skew_method == 'farrow'``; must be a positive odd "
"integer."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.calibrate_foreground.calibrate_foreground:24 of
msgid "**y** -- Calibrated interleaved signal."
msgstr ""

#: adctoolbox.timeinterleave.calibrate_foreground.calibrate_foreground:29 of
msgid ""
"The order matters: offset is removed first (before gain normalization), then "
"gain is applied, and skew correction is last — mixing channels only at the "
"fractional-delay interpolation stage preserves the per-channel amplitude "
"balance that the prior two steps just enforced."
msgstr ""
